The home in Canelands, KwaZulu
Natal was engulfed in flames when paramedics arrived. According to Reaction Unit South
Africa (RUSA) the received multiple calls from residents in the area reporting
the blaze. When reaction officers and
paramedics arrived on scene the occupants had evacuated the house before the
arrival of first responders. “Whilst conducting a search for
animals in the yard, reaction officers found a man attempting to remove an illegal
electricity connection from the rear of the burning building,” said RUSA in a
statement. No injuries were reported but the
home was destroyed. 